L12 Shiny II

Data Visualization (STAT 302)

YOUR NAME

Overview

The goal of this lab is to reinforce and extend the shiny basics covered in lesson 3 and lesson 4. We will be building upon the CDCapp from the previous lab by adding widgets and the corresponding reactive coding.

The challenge utilizes information from the webinar video and applies a layout found in the application layout guide - link from lesson 3. The challenge simply extends the shiny app that is built in Exercise 2.

Dataset

To complete this lab we require the familiar cdc.txt dataset. As a reminder the dataset variables are

  • genhlth - How would you rate your general health? (excellent, very good, good, fair, poor)
  • exerany - Have you exercised in the past month? (1=yes, 0=no)
  • hlthplan - Do you have some form of health coverage? (1=yes, 0=no)
  • smoke100 - Have you smoked at least 100 cigarettes in your life time? (1=yes, 0=no)
  • height - height in inches
  • weight - weight in pounds
  • wtdesire - weight desired in pounds
  • age - in years
  • gender - m for male and f for female


Submission Guidelines

You will be submitting a zip file that contains all app directories (each app gets a directory/file). See the shiny App Labs page on Canvas for complete instructions. Please only include shiny app directories/files. The zip file should follow our standard naming convention (e.g. Kuyper_Arend_L12.zip.


Exercises

Complete the following exercises.


Exercise 1

Work through lesson 3 and lesson 4 which both contain an exercise for practice. In this case, the exercise for lesson 4 simply builds directly upon lesson 3’s exercise. Submit one shiny app that corresponds with the completion of the exercises for lessons 3 and 4.


Exercise 2

Beginning with your app.R script from Exercise 2 of the previous lab (L11), add two more widgets with reactive coding to build the shiny app pictured below. For a closer look you can access the shiny app at https://amkuyper.shinyapps.io/CDCapp2-L12/.


Challenge

Not required, but hope you try.

Modify the app.R script from Exercise 2 above by adding a "None" option for the radio buttons widget that sets the fill to skyblue. The widget for the number of bins should be animated (i.e. press play and it will cycle through the slider bar’s values). Also, alter the layout to include a tab set panel with one panel showing the plot and the other panel displaying a summary for the variable and fill widgets. See the pictures below for clarification or for a closer look access the shiny app at https://amkuyper.shinyapps.io/CDC_challenge_L12/.
